by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-2-201, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(f)
(1) Notwithstanding another law to the contrary, a local legislative body
for a county that has adopted a charter form of government may require:
(A) Elections for the county board of education to be held at the
same time and on the same election cycle as elections for members of
the local legislative body for the county;
(B) Members of the county board of education to have successive
terms of office if members of the local legislative body for the county have
successive terms of office; and
(C) Members of the county board of education to have the same
term limits as members of the local legislative body for the county.
(2) This subsection (f) does not vacate or abridge a term of office for a
member on a county board of education.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
